# Quality-gate recipes — MERGE into your repo's root justfile.
# `just` is the cross-platform task runner (install: `cargo install just`,
# `brew install just`, or `scoop install just`). Simpler than make (no .PHONY,
# no tab traps) and OS-agnostic.
#
# `just check` is the ONE command an agent runs to self-verify — all local gates
# (Tier 1-2) on demand. Tier 3 (mutation) is CI-only, never here. Single source
# of truth: lefthook.yml defines the commands; this just runs both tiers now
# (lefthook's hooks fire on commit/push — an iterating agent needs them without
# committing). Any failing gate aborts the recipe non-zero, so the agent keeps
# fixing. See rules/agent/autonomy.md for the loop this powers.
#
# NB portability: this entry point is cross-platform, but a gate it invokes may
# not be (e.g. a bash scripts/rust-fmt.sh). CI is the authority and runs on
# Linux; local Windows devs can lean on CI for any non-portable gate.

# Run all local gates. Iterate until green before handing back.
check:
    lefthook run pre-commit --all-files
    lefthook run pre-push --all-files
